node.text:
Footage from 2012 hightimes to 2014 emerald cup. We did different shows debuting the Migars. 

too watch the full video go to my YouTube channel Jean Carlos Migars

Thanks to everyone that supported something bold and new that was completely different but it took guts to showcase a cannabis cigar to an industry that never knew they could exist.

@midnight.roots @marislims_shells 

.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
Smoking a cigar is not smoking a cigarette. Now smoking a Migar is not like smoking a preroll.

Taking a shot to tequila isn’t like sipping on a glass of Merlot or champagne.

There is a difference that distinguishes the experience.

Too smoke the finer things in life you need to indulge yourself in the experience and meditate in the moment.

Takes patience in mind. Who’s in a rush to enjoy something with class and sophistication.

@midnight.roots @marislims_shells 

.
.
.
.
#class #status #finerthingsinlife #cigarsnob #cigarmagazine #hemp

node.text:
I remember way back when I started growing cannabis I was in my garage always researching as much as I could to learn how to grow. All we had were forums sites that growers would go into to share their knowledge. These days there were zero influencers no one was really sharing much. One day Subcool popped up on my feed on YouTube. We always have to pay homage to those that paved the way and never forget what they did for our industry.

When sub popped up I ran straight to my local dispensary harborside in Oakland and got 5 packs of his seeds.

When he showed that ace of spades, vortex, qrazy train, cheesequake, agent orange and jilly bean. On you tube I had to get me some of his gear. So I headed straight to harborside in Oakland when he announce he would make a drop on the weednerd show.

After testing the strains I instantly started posting his gear on Facebook and tagged myself as a weednerd Jean carlos tga. I wasn’t affiliated with tga but just out of respect to showcase his gear as something special I put tga on my name. 
3 years after in 2013 subcool recognized my grow skills and we met for the first time at 2013 sf hightimes cup. 
I’ll never forget when I walked up to his booth. He was talking to a couple about his seeds, he had so much passion explaining about them. I had my camera on him after they left I walked up to him and said hey sub do you know who I am. He said no brother but how can I help you.? My Response: I’m Jean Carlos tga! His response in a pound voice (hey jilly! Jilly!! )It’s he’s Carlos tga!!!
Come over in here brother ! Gave me a big big hug and said great to finally meet you. I was humbled and honored. Sub said to mzjill (jilly it’s jean Carlos!)
To me I was just a grower in my garage that respected his gear but never knew he would take me in just so humble to meet me. when I was the one that looked up to him. I have some video footage of that day, we sat down and I showed him my magars for the first time. Gonna put a small video together of that day. I wanted to hang out longer but cameras wanted to interview him but it was Definatly a memory I’ll never forget.

We can’t forget the pioneers. Thanks to @mzjillgrower @mzjill420 ✊🏽

Curred cannabis leaf shell packed with @midnight.roots award winning flowers.

Hand rolled and cured lime a true cigar defending from 4 generations of Nicaragua cigar tradition.

Song. Tito Puente timbalero the writer and composer of the song with a Mambo rythm Cuban Charanga style flute playing.

@marislims_shells 
.
.
.
.
.
#hechoamano #torcedor #cigarrolling #tradition

node.text:
Our candela shells coming soon made from our cured leaves. Things take time to develop we spare no expense in working hard to develop something unique and special. Thanks to my team and family for helping me innovate and never stop developing. Don’t settle keep grinding think and visualize. Let’s celebrate the end to this locked down and pandemic. Get out and have a special day with friend.

@marislims_shells @carlitos_migars @_gregthebarber @midnight.roots @organitips

.
.
.
.
.
